      "content": "it still feels like we're dancing around it. if a reporter from a major tech outlet asks us directly, \"Was this a mistake caused by a human error in S3 configuration?\" and we give them a vague answer about \"internal processes,\" won't that make us look like we're hiding something? wouldn't it be more effective to just be blunt so we don't lose all user trust if the truth leaks?",
